The square shown is divided into 4 congruent rectangles. If the perimeter of the square is 144 units, what is the perimeter of one of the four congruent rectangles?

\begin{center}
    \begin{asy}
    size(8cm);
defaultpen(linewidth(0.8));
draw(unitsquare);
draw((0,0.25)--(1,0.25)); draw((0,0.5)--(1,0.5)); draw((0,0.75)--(1,0.75));
    \end{asy}
\end{center}

}

\textbf{Answer:} $AB$ consists of 24 segments each of length 20 feet, and so it measures $24\cdot20=480$ feet. Similarly, $DE=480$ feet. Each of $BC$, $CD$, $EF$, and $FA$ measure 62 feet. In total, the perimeter is $480+480+62+62+62+62=\boxed{1208}$ feet.
}
